    &lt;Title&gt;Dr talked at me, not to me&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Anonymous&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;Rushed appt - went to get test results and the consultant did not introduce himself, shake my hand or give me any eye contact!  He filled in forms whilst talking AT me and told me that I needed surgery.  No discussion about why it had to be surgery, no discussion about possible alternative treatment, no asking me if I had questions / concerns etc.  I came out with paperwork and a surgery time line of 6 - 8 weeks.  

The nurse / CSW in clinic was clearly 'dancing around' the consultant, she could not get passed his chair and rather than ask him, she climbed over the examination bed to get to the other side of the room!  She could have fallen and hurt herself!  That is a serious health and safety issue, that no nurse should have to deal with.  I watched on as the consultant  asked her things without looking up at her.    I came out of the appt wondering what had hit me and why I had not been referred to a specialist nurse who could answer my questions etc.

Needless to say, I am seeking a 2nd opinion.  Very unhappy with the speed and manner in which I was 'dealt' with.  I thought these days of impersonal, &amp;amp;quot;Dr knows best&amp;amp;quot; attitudes had gone; alas, they are very much still the norm in this ENT dept.

I also notice that the hospital only appear to respond to positive feedback on this web page - if they looked into the negative comments they would soon fix the issues that we patients are reporting and so improve the service.  Negative feedback is an opportunity to improve - use it!&lt;/CommentText&gt;
